snippet.textDisplay: Love the channel guys! here is a tip my grandma taught me. Use weed wacker string under the edge of rubber moldings and weatherstrip so that it will lift the rubber and you wont get a paint line. Also you have to put a base color down first to cover the different colors, white door and black fender will look different when you spray red or any finish color over it. The door will look like a bright red and the fender will look dark red, but if you prime both they will look identical. I hope Grandmas tips help
